In response to Mr. Felder's posting, and for anyone else who'd like to
have it, here is the electronic version of the ACM Membership Application:



Thank you for your interest in ACM.  You may use the following application
to apply for membership.  Please fill in all the necessary information and
place an'X' in the spaces for any desired publications or Special Interest
Groups.  If you have any questions you may contact the Member Services
department at ACMHELP@ACM.ORG or call 212-626-0500. When you have completed
the application, please return it to ACMHELP@ACM.ORG or mail it to ACM
Member Services, 1515 Broadway, 17th Floor, New York NY 10036-5701 USA.
Please be sure to include your payment whether responding via email or
postal service.

There are four sections of the application:

    1) Membership Fees and Categories
    2) Publications
    3) Special Interest Groups
    4) Payment Information
______________________________________________________________________



ACM MEMBERSHIP APPLICATION

You may use this application to:  1) Join ACM and take advantage of the
special publication and SIG rates for ACM members; 2) Join the Special
Interest Group(s) of your choice at the SIG Member (non-ACM member) rates;
individuals joining SIGS using these rates are not entitled to ACM membership
privileges.

ACM membership includes a subscription to the monthly magazine
Communications of the ACM.  Membership dues include $32.00 ($24.00 for
students) toward a subscription to Communications of the ACM.
_____________________________________________________________________________

1) MEMBERSHIP FEES AND CATEGORIES

    Please place an "X" next to the dues for the membership category
    desired.  Your choices of membership are: Voting, Associate, Student
    Joint (with IEEE-CS), Joint (with other international society),
    Spouse and Affiliate.

-Voting Member     ____$79
You must subscribe to the Purposes of ACM; have attained professional
stature as demonstrated by intellectual competence and ethical conduct
in the arts and sciences of information processing; and must satisfy
at least one of the following requirements: Bachelor's degree or
equivalent level of education, or four full-time years of experience.
