3) SPECIAL INTEREST GROUPS

Some ACM Special Interest Groups (SIGs) offer special Member Plus services --
an opportunity for you to receive specific conference proceedings at rates
significantly below the already discounted ACM member rate.  You must be
a member of a SIG to take advantage of its added services, e.g., you must be
a member of SIGACT to purchase the SPAA Conference proceedings at the special
Member Plus rate, you must be a member of SIGCHI to purchase the CHI Member
Plus package, etc.

There are now two types of SIGGRAPH membership -- regular, which provides the
services listed, and new SIGGRAPH LITE, for those who only wish to receive
the SIGGRAPH newsletter and a discount to the annual SIGGRAPH conference.
Either SIGGRAPH membership option entitles individuals to purchase the
SIGGRAPH Member Plus package.


